  "prompt": "What gets you noticed enough by the company to get hired as a journalist if you didn't get a degree in journalism?",
  "response": "To get noticed as a journalist without a journalism degree, you can:\n\n1. Build a strong portfolio\n- Start a blog or personal website\n- Write for online publications\n- Create a compelling collection of writing samples\n\n2. Gain relevant experience\n- Write for local newspapers or magazines\n- Contribute to online news sites\n- Start a podcast or YouTube channel\n- Freelance writing\n- Internships in media or communications\n\n3. Develop key skills\n- Strong writing and communication abilities\n- Research and investigative skills\n- Understanding of digital media\n- Proficiency in social media\n- Basic photography and video editing\n- Knowledge of current events\n\n4. Network\n- Attend journalism conferences\n- Connect with journalists on LinkedIn\n- Join professional journalism associations\n- Engage with media professionals on social platforms\n\n5. Learn and demonstrate\n- Take online courses in journalism\n- Get certifications\n- Participate in workshops\n- Show passion and commitment to storytelling\n\n6. Create a unique angle or specialty\n- Focus on a specific niche or topic\n- Develop expertise in an area of interest\n- Pitch unique story ideas\n\n7. Use digital platforms\n- Build a strong online presence\n- Showcase your work on platforms like Medium\n- Create a compelling LinkedIn profile\n\nPersistence, quality work, and continuously improving your skills are key.",
